texts.text: Ugh... No, not yet...
I... I will not fall to you just yet...!!
(This one's body and soul... They have gone beyond their limits...)
(And yet he still clings while bearing this burden...)

*Groan*
No, how...?!
Why...? Why are you not burning?! A mere human, how...?!
Uriel... Please, one final blow...!
Adramelech...
Taste my wrath! The power of my holy fire!
>Yoji's body begins to beam with light.
No, this is...!
Megakin, now!
>Megakin's demon pierces Adramelech!
*Scream*
You... If only I had regained my full strength as the sun god...!
I will not fall... Not to these vermin...!
I suppose HIS power was not as great as I expected it to be.
Bah, no matter...!
My other resurrection schemes are well underway.
I will be the one that gets the last laugh in the end.
Your blasted God will fall and this world will be remade...
I will revive myself as many times as necessary.
I will return stronger, more complete... Next time...!
>Adramelech disappears.
We did it...
Yeah, that was close.
Imagine if Yoji weren't here...
Yes, Yoji...
*Wince*
>Yoji's body has stopped shining with light.
Yoji?!
All good. He's still alive...
Y-Yeah...!
Oh, thank goodness...
Aight, all that's left to do is to head back...!
Liberators.
That voice...
I commend your efforts in defeating Adramelech.
Y-You're here?! Yo, why didn't you fight that thing yourself...?!
This is only my avatar. This is only a fraction of my power as well.
This is not my actual self.
Aight, whatever. Then what's the deal? We're takin' Yoji back, if you don't mind.
So be it. That one showed more strength than I expected.
As well as the rest of you.
You are God's instruments as well...
>Uriel's avatar vanishes as he utters those words...
I'm sure we're all tired, but just a little more.
Let's get out of there and go home!
*Sigh*
Okay, I don't care if it's Meat Balloon or Megakin,
someone help carry Yoji!
He's really hurt, so we need to get him to a hospital ASAP!
Yeah, and we gotta let the kids know too.
Yes. We told them that we would too so...
>A few days after the Aura Gate disappeared...
Again, thank you... You especially, Megakin.
Hey, you all good now?
Yes. But the children are still treating me like their patient.
Aight. And just as things start settlin' down, we get all this snow.
Ain't there a way to do this remotely?

*Chuckle*
As expected from a Megatuber.
But I wanted to see and thank you in person.
Oh, it does seem like I was followed though.
>Yoji turns to look at the children playing in the snow.
You ain't gonna disappear on us like that again, right?
I mean, you got a record now so...
You know just where to hit me...
You gonna keep your job...?
I will. I've been doing this for so long, it'd be hard to change now.
Right...
Ah, but you really do still speak your mind like you did back then.
Don't worry, I'm seeing things much clearer now.
I'm looking for ways to help the ones that care about me,
so that we can all get through the darkness together.
Yeah. Do that. Yo, those kids still really need you.
Right... But even now, that angel's words still rings with me,
and a part of me still wants to sacrifice myself to fight evil.
I don't actually think that his goals were entirely wrong.
And it aligns with what I believe in as well.
Whoa! Hold up!
What happened to "I cannot die here..."?!
That was because I believed what you said.
I... I believed that we could defeat that evil together.
And I thought that I'd be able to see the children one more time.
But that is separate from any desire to actually live.
I don't possess the powers that you and your friends do.
So if it means that I can protect the world these children live in,
then I will surely do it again.
It's my purpose... Or rather, for the sake of their futures.
To me, there is a vast gap between these two ideas.
Do you think that it's foolish or that I'm making a mistake?
Yo, I don't think it's a matter of right or wrong.
I just wanted you to think about finding a different way.
But I'm just glad that you started thinkin' about how others feel too.
Yes.
As humans, we must think about what we can do for ourselves each day,
and venture forth into a vast, unknown future.
We may feel lonely and doubtful...
But I see that it's important to be there with someone. For someone.
That may be part of the reason why we exist here in the first place.
Yeah... Now you're startin' to sound like a real priest.
Ever the comedian.
Yo, the sun being that hot sucked,
but it could've been a little warmer today, you know?
You see the forecast? Yo, we're right back in the dead of winter.
And the snow's gonna come and go for the next two days...
This may be bad...
The children might start catching colds if they're not careful.
Father! Look! We made a snowman!
This one's a bunny! Father...!
Hey, they're still talking, so be a little more patient.
They're callin' for you, Father.
Yes. Let's leave it here for now.
I'll drop by with the children again sometime soon.
Aight, sounds good.
And I'll head over when I have somethin' new in store for y'all.
Take care. Bye.
Aight. Later.
Father, look! A small snowman! Isn't it cute?
It is, and it's very well made.
Hey, look here too!
Slow down. You'll slip and fall if you're not careful.
Okay!
>Yoji and the children all laugh as they play together.
>Each smile even seemed to glow like a small, bright sun.
If the sun shines too brightly, we all get burned.
We need a sun that ain't too hot or too cold.
And we need to be connected to others to live on...
We all need each other. That's what I believe...
